<div id="review_2394670770" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2394670770" />
    <a title="Nick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14612139-nick"><img alt="Nick" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1353248506p2/14612139.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2394670770?book_show_action=true">May 17, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nick" href="/user/show/14612139-nick">Nick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780676972924" href="/book/show/1120831.The_Dream_of_Scipio">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14612139-nick?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14612139-nick?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2394670770" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8775364405604124701">I rarely ever give more then three stars, so it really took me some self convincing to finally give this book that five star rating it deserves. <br/><br/>Any explanation or summary of the book or detailed description would do this book injustice; it would take me hours to only find the right words let alone use them to forge a review of such a kind worthy of its material. <br/><br/>In stead I want to limit myself to the big feeling I got from the book; even though the book interweaves three stories that are centur</span>
  <span id="freeText8775364405604124701" style="display:none">I rarely ever give more then three stars, so it really took me some self convincing to finally give this book that five star rating it deserves. <br /><br />Any explanation or summary of the book or detailed description would do this book injustice; it would take me hours to only find the right words let alone use them to forge a review of such a kind worthy of its material. <br /><br />In stead I want to limit myself to the big feeling I got from the book; even though the book interweaves three stories that are centuries apart, linked only through very flimsy connection brought upon mostly by taking place in the same location and words echoing through the ages; it still manages to be a whole. That left me in awe after only a few dozen pages and did so until the end. The tone of the stories flowed together so perfectly to create a symphony as it were, and culminating in a message that could either be ironically simple or deceivingly simple given the contrast of the philosophy discussed throughout the book. <br /><br />Perhaps I was the perfect crowd, as a historian, an emotional and sensitive person with some self delusions of a having a role in the preserving of the cultural and intellectual wealth of society yet accompanied with the ever enduring doubts whether this truly serves anything; one can easily get why I felt connected to all three of the stories main characters. In a way they are a mirror to what each path can lead to and it forces me to ask, what form of person will I become in my life and to what extent do I want a legacy to go at a cost of my humanity. <br /><br />One for the top ten lists </span>
  <a data-text-id="8775364405604124701" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


